# Docker

> Container platform for building, shipping, and running applications in isolated environments.

---

## Overview

Docker provides:
- **Containers**: Lightweight, portable runtime environments
- **Images**: Immutable application snapshots
- **Compose**: Multi-container orchestration
- **Registry**: Image distribution (Docker Hub)
- **Isolation**: Process, network, and filesystem separation

---

## Why Docker

| Benefit | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Consistency | Same environment everywhere |
| Isolation | No dependency conflicts |
| Portability | Run anywhere Docker runs |
| Efficiency | Share OS kernel, lighter than VMs |
| Reproducibility | Version-controlled infrastructure |

