## Core Concepts

### Images vs Containers

```
Image (Blueprint)           Container (Running Instance)
├── Read-only layers       ├── Image + writable layer
├── Built from Dockerfile  ├── Can be started/stopped
├── Stored in registry     ├── Isolated process
└── Shared across hosts    └── Ephemeral by default
```

### Dockerfile

```dockerfile
# Base image
FROM node:20-alpine

# Working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy dependency files first (layer caching)
COPY package*.json ./

# Install dependencies
RUN npm ci --only=production

# Copy application code
COPY . .

# Build application
RUN npm run build

# Expose port
EXPOSE 3000

# Runtime command
CMD ["node", "dist/main.js"]
```

