## Essential Commands

### Image Management

```bash
# Build image from Dockerfile
docker build -t myapp:1.0 .
docker build -t myapp:1.0 -f Dockerfile.prod .

# List images
docker images

# Pull from registry
docker pull node:20-alpine

# Push to registry
docker push myrepo/myapp:1.0

# Remove image
docker rmi myapp:1.0
docker image prune  # Remove unused images
```

### Container Management

```bash
# Run container
docker run myapp:1.0
docker run -d myapp:1.0                    # Detached
docker run -p 3000:3000 myapp:1.0          # Port mapping
docker run -v $(pwd):/app myapp:1.0        # Volume mount
docker run -e NODE_ENV=production myapp    # Environment var
docker run --name my-container myapp:1.0   # Named container
docker run -it myapp:1.0 /bin/sh           # Interactive shell

# Container lifecycle
docker ps                     # List running
docker ps -a                  # List all
docker stop <container>       # Stop gracefully
docker start <container>      # Start stopped
docker restart <container>    # Restart
docker rm <container>         # Remove stopped
docker rm -f <container>      # Force remove running

# Container inspection
docker logs <container>       # View logs
docker logs -f <container>    # Follow logs
docker exec -it <container> sh  # Shell into running container
docker inspect <container>    # Detailed info
```

